-- Monte Paschi put up 1.67 bln euros as collateral for Nomura trade-prospectus
-- 
-- Fri Jun 06, 2014 08:43AM EDT
-- None



MILAN, June 6 (Reuters) - Italian lender Banca Monte dei Paschi di Siena <BMPS.MI> had to put up 1.67 billion euros ($2.27 billion) by way of collateral for a 2009 derivative trade with Nomura <8604.T> as of end-April, the bank said on Friday in the prospectus for its upcoming rights issue.

